            . I am the wife of William Fears, a <rs id="t18270531-245-viclabel1312" type="occupation">shoemaker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270531-245-victim1352 t18270531-245-viclabel1312"></join> - we live in <placeName id="t18270531-245-crimeloc1313">Tothill-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18270531-245-crimeloc1313" type="placeName" value="Tothill-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18270531-245-crimeloc1313" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270531-245-off1310 t18270531-245-crimeloc1313"></join>. The prisoners came in on the 30th of May - the man asked for a pair of boots to fit his wife; I tried on a pair - the man sat on a chair, and put his arm across; he took off a pair of boots, and put them into his basket, while I was trying a pair on his wife; he then objected that they were not a right and left - I showed a pair that were - they would not have them, and went away, saying they would come again in an hour; I said nothing to them, as I was alone; I followed them about four doors, then took hold of the man, and said he had a pair of shoes in his basket - he denied it; I brought them back, and the constable found them.</p>
               <p>
            
